                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "Instead of reducing the accuracy by 5% per rank, each rank increases spread by a specific value per rank depending on the weapon."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "source": "local-wiki-sqlite",
                  "pageTitle": "Heavy Caliber",
                  "pageId": 233549,
                  "revisionId": 2720779,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "Damage bonus stacks additively with similar mods, such as Serration ."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "source": "local-wiki-sqlite",
                  "pageTitle": "Heavy Caliber",
                  "pageId": 233549,
                  "revisionId": 2720779,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "Since the two stack additively and Heavy Caliber costs 2 more mod capacity for the same bonus, combining the two is slightly less efficient in terms of damage per capacity cost. Maxed Serration grants +11.79% bonus damage per 1 mod capacity, while maxed Heavy Caliber grants +10.31% bonus damage per mod capacity. Combining the two, Serration and Heavy Caliber grant +11% bonus damage per 1 mod capacity, which is +0.79% less bonus damage per capacity than Serration alone."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "source": "local-wiki-sqlite",
                  "pageTitle": "Heavy Caliber",
                  "pageId": 233549,
                  "revisionId": 2720779,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "Added spread is not affected by bonuses that increase accuracy, such as Twitch or Guided Ordnance ."
                }
              },
              {
                "reviewStatus": "draft",
                "provenance": {
                  "source": "local-wiki-sqlite",
                  "pageTitle": "Heavy Caliber",
                  "pageId": 233549,
                  "revisionId": 2720779,
                  "section": "Notes",
                  "excerpt": "For example, a Braton with Heavy Caliber and Twitch will have a max deviation of 5.0 × (1 - 40% ) + 2.97 = 6 degrees."
                }
              },
